    <p>3.5. HTML Forms
        We can create a form in HTML by using the form opening and closing tags.
        Inside our Form element, we have inputs and a submit button. Some of our inputs will be of type text, and
        our submit button will actually be an input of type submit.</p>
    <p>Form tags
        When we work with HTML forms in the real world, there are three attributes that we need to add to our opening form tag.
        The <form> tag takes the three attributes: Method, Action, and enctype.</p>

